comments.body:
1. Confirm the affected set first

use POI

db.GeoLocation.countDocuments({
FeatureClass: 80,
FeatureCode:  "PPL",
IsPostal:     false,
Searchable:   false,
CountryCode:  "US"
})
Should return 148768 count

2. Update

db.GeoLocation.updateMany(
{
FeatureClass: 80,
FeatureCode:  "PPL",
IsPostal:     false,
Searchable:   false,
CountryCode:  "US"
},
{
$set: { IsCity: true, Searchable: true }
}
)

should return :
{
acknowledged: true,
insertedId: null,
matchedCount: 148768,
modifiedCount: 148768,
upsertedCount: 0
}

Running following script on STG to enable the list below to appear on geosearch

db.GeoLocation.updateMany(
{
FeatureClass: 80,
FeatureCode: "PPL",
IsPostal: false,
Searchable: false,
$or: [
{
CountryCode: {
$in: [
"AU",
"CA",
"FR",
"GB",
"IE",
"MX",
"US"
]
}
},
{
"Ids.GeoNameId": {
$in: ["292968", "3511632", "3572972", "12362529"]
}
}
]
},
{
$set: { IsCity: true, Searchable: true }
}
)

Inserted documents for the following two records as they are not PPL type

12362529 - Playa Herradura, CR
3572972  - Warwick Parish, BM

@Joshua Marquess @Brian Pugh Hi guys, I’ve created this ticket to update the location of the is_hotdeal value used in the New Booking API. It’s currently coming over in an unexpected location and causing the GolfNow Hot Deal Green Fee behavior on the tee sheet to not work properly when testing a course using the new booking API for trade rate sets.

Happy to provide any other details that may be needed here. Can we fit this one into an upcoming sprint?

cc: @Jeff Sykes @Dewan Kabir

issues.description:
Need to expose .well-known/openai-apps-challenge to OpenAI in order to validate domain during app submission

app.MapGet(".well-known/openai-apps-challenge", (IConfiguration config) =>
{
var token = config["ChallengeToken"] ?? string.Empty;
return Results.Text(token, "text/plain");
});
